reviews:
This is a really lovely hotel, with fantastic staff. We went in a big group to celebrate a friend's birthday and nothing was too much trouble. All our different questions and requests were dealt with efficiently and with kindness. We were made to feel very welcome.

The rooms are on the small side, but very comfortable, with lovely beds and pillows. The bathrooms are clean with plenty of towels and hot water. The continental breakfast was delicious, with croissants, pain au chocolat and choices of cold meat and cheese. Although there is not a restaurant or bar, you can buy hot and cold drinks from reception.

The location is very convenient, with two metro stations within ten minutes' walk. The area is quiet, with some lovely local shops tucked just behind the hotel. We felt perfectly safe popping out alone for a wander.

Overall, a great hotel and outstanding staff. Thank you so much for making our stay special.

Good location and average service but ok for one night that I spent as didn’t have lot of stuff; I’m not sure how would I move with more things because the room was really small. Breakfast is very poor and it has to be improved. I’m not sure that I would stay there when visiting Paris again, only if I have no other options.

We booked via Secret Escapes and got a nice deal. The rooms are small but cute, daily room service is good, location is super safe, reception open 24 hrs, iron available on request and decent small breakfast. We personally had a good experience, specially keeping the price in mind. We were struggling to find a mid-range hotel in peak summer holidays and found this bargain deal on Secret Escapes.

I was in Paris for a conference for a couple of days and needed a reasonably priced hotel for my stay. Hotel Gaston was within budget and the hotel was quite modern and very clean. The staff are so friendly that the hotel leaves you with an impression of old fashioned charm, they always remember their guests and make an effort if you need assistance. I would highly recommend staying here.

Average hotel.
What you pay is what you get - you pay for 3 stars, you get 3.
Room was clean but tiny.
Shower head didn’t work so the shower didn’t hold.
Not enough water pressure
Sink drainage doesn’t work properly so water collected in the sink.
Staff ask to hold the room keys whilst you’re out (a bit off putting).
Staff aren’t as friendly as expected.
Location is quite good, not close to Paris attractions but close enough to the metro (10 min walk).
Seems like a safe area of Paris..
would I stay again? Probably not.

I was searching for an economical place for my daughter and I to stay for a last-minute trip to Paris during her Spring Break. When I came across the artsy, modern style of Hotel Gaston I knew it was the one for us - we are big fans of modern design.

Upon arrival, I was especially pleased to find the hotel is conveniently located in a quiet neighborhood of Paris, close to a few restaurants and grocery stores, as well as metro and bus stations. Our room was small, but perfectly adequate for what we needed as we don’t spend lots of time in a hotel room when on vacation. Our bathroom was small as well - only room for one at a time, but again, was perfectly adequate. We fell in love with the (almost) floor-to-ceiling window in our room that we could swing open and fully let the sights and sounds of this quietly bustling area of the city in. We fell in love with the modern design of our room as well as the fantastic artwork in the hallways of each floor. Really fun and creative!

We mainly interacted with three staff members who were each very friendly and went out of their way to be as helpful to us as possible. Being foreigners in a new country, we had lots of questions and needed quite a bit of transportation guidance at the start. A+ to the Hotel Gaston staff. Housekeeping came daily and remade our bed as well as vacuumed, emptied trash, and left fresh towels. We opted for the two twin beds pushed together and the mattresses were very comfortable! I wouldn’t hesitate to book a stay with Hotel Gaston again on a return trip to Paris!

If you are looking for a "boutique hotel" that is squeaky clean, uniquely Parisian and very intimate, this is it. We stayed 6 nights in room 506 (one of the Privilege Rooms), accessible via a tiny but beautiful blue lift. The room is impeccable and smells so fresh every time you walk in. The bed with 4 pillows and the softest bedding is incredibly comfortable and is just perfect to rest your body after a long day of walking. The room is very tiny, but the space is designed so thoughtfully and beautifully that you just have to look in the right places to find everything you need right there in the room. There's a nespresso machine, a safe, a luggage rack, an open wardrobe, several charging points, a desk with a chair, fog-free bathroom mirror with the cutest bowtie on it. The highlight is undoubtedly, the spectacular view from the Juliet-style balcony. There was a wonderful lady at reception who handled our check-in and was there for most of our stay except the weekend, when we checked out. 5 stars for the non-intrusive, friendly service.

Check-in and check-out are the quickest (two minutes tops), which we greatly appreciated. We would recommend doing the online check-in before arriving.

Definitely pick Gaston over other hotels in the area like the Novotel, which is very close by but is on a much busier junction. Hotel Gaston is in a quiet, beautiful area, which you'll surely appreciate.

The only negative, perhaps, was the washbasin sink, which got very easily clogged. This was cleaned by housekeeping everyday but the issue persisted. This, however, did not diminish the quality of our stay and we're looking forward to going back to Hotel Gaston the next time we're in Paris!

The hotel is situated in a very friendly and “safe” neighborhood. The entire staff is very friendly and helpful. Breakfast is according to French standard very good - the waitress always ready to bring you extras. The reception is manned 24/7. The rooms are not that big - but you’re not supposed to spend much time in your hotel room when you’re visiting Paris anyway. The hotel and the rooms are clean - but it’s a old building, so don’t expect high tech rooms with brand new furnitures. It is one of our best value for money experiences according to hotels.

Stayed with little one and brothers. The hotel is located in the 13 arrondissement, so away from the hustle and bustle and calm. Leafy suburb with shops and restaurants close by.

Reception were very friendly and we received a warm welcome. Breakfast is French, so nothing hot just pastries. The lounge is airy and spacious.

Room wise, small which is typically French. We had a shower and my brothers had a bath. Amenities were of decent quality and replaced regularly. The lift is small and can only take one or two people comfortably.

All good, there were some available umbrellas at the reception that you can take for free.
By some reason the fire alarm went on around 10 am but it was false alarm. Anyways got a bit scare but very good overall

firstly the good things about this hotel is that it is a very nice area of the city. The rooms are more or less nice although a little small but we knew to expect this in Paris. The Bed however was very very comfortable especially the pillows. It liked the quirky designs in the corridors and room.

The downsides were having our room key taken away from us every time we left the hotel for the day . whilst we understood that this was a precaution this kind of mistrust and automatic disciplinary attitude towards guest's puzzled us and did not make for an completely welcoming atmosphere.

Whilst the reception and cleaning staff were friendly , I think there could just be a couple of small changes made that would make the whole experience seem a bit more generous and relaxed . small things like free use of umbrella in the lobby without instantly demanding a deposit for it , a free drink for the guest when they arrive perhaps? even if its just water with some lemon ( thats cheap to provide but feels welcoming ) nothing fancy . I would have loved to have much bigger and softer towels in the bathrooms rather then those small scrappy ones that you cant even wrap around you , and a conditioner as well as shampoo would have been nice . Finally maybe something hot to eat at breakfast time ( maybye eggs?) .

The one final point is that , unfortunately there was a fire alarm during our stay which was a mistake and could not be helped however , when we came down the fire exit stairway we had to go through what seemed to be a storage room which really wasn't clear especially in the dark and in our confused state it would have been quite dangerous had there been a real fire .

The hotel was located in an ideal location where there was metro stations nearby to access central Paris.

We booked the room for three people, the room itself was fairly spacious and modern. For the price you pay it is much more modern and clean than what you would get in a central area of Paris city centre.

The only downside was that per arrival we were informed by a member a staff that breakfast was included when asked the question. But then we were shocked to find we had to cough up the fee of around 12 euros a day per person for the breakfast. Which I may add was not worth it at all. All that was available was a few pastries and different breads, for the price I paid I would expect something more substantial.

Overall a good hotel, staff were friendly and accommodating but I would highly recommend to avoid the breakfast not value for money.

The Hotel Gaston is in the 17th Arrondissement of Paris, not far from 2 subway stations which can take you anywhere in Paris in short order. The hotel is part of an older building which has been updated with modern appointments. The rooms are small, as expected in this urban district but comfortable. The staff is very helpful and the breakfasts were wonderful. It is close enough to Montmartre and Sacre'Cour Basilica that we walked back one evening, seeing a beautiful and lively evening unfold on the eve of Spring.

It was a nice room and the receptionists were very friendly and helpful.
The hotel is close to all shopping street 15/20min by walk.
The downside is that our room was across the lift and we heard all noises and people waiting for the elevator.

This is a great find.The rooms are decorated in a cool way, they were spotlessly clean. The beds are super comfy. Staff are so helpful and friendly. The breakfast choice is limited but good quality. The hotel is in a great location with lots of restaurants and boulangeries nearby and easy to walk into the central tourist areas (20 mins to Arc de Triomphe) or get on the metro.
Chez Maxence does excellent crepes nearby.

Friends of ours recommended Hotel Gaston to us, so we tried it for a 6 day visit in November 2019. We found the hotel to be in a very safe location. There are numerous restaurants in the area, and it is a 5 minute walk to Wagram Metro stop. The staff were unusually friendly and helpful. On several occasions they made things way easier for us by making phone calls, explaining things on the phone in French to drivers or other people to help us out. The room was very clean and comfortable (yes, not large). The breakfast was well done, and had a variety of foods. we will stay here again. The bed was comfy, the shower was very good, and it is on a pretty tree lined street.

We bought a Paris week through Groupon, with air and hotel, and did our own activities. Hotel Gaston is charming and small, 6 floors, with a tiny elevator, and our tiny but quiet clean room had lovely tall windows that overlooked the adjacent street park. The daily breakfast is 7-10, with a variety of coffees and teas, some baked goods and cheeses and cold cuts, 2 juice choices and packaged yogurt, and fruit. The staff was helpful. The location is not the nearest to major Metro lines, but with a bit of walking, you do have a few options. There’s plenty of eateries and shops nearby, and our street itself is quiet & pretty. We ordered the airport shuttle on our departure, and the usual 40-min drive to Orly took 2 hours, with traffic and light rain and 2 other pickups. So, if you order it, do ask for an earlier pickup if you wish to arrive the recommended 3 hours before an international flight instead of 2 hours. All in all, a very pleasant stay & place!

Lovely quirky hotel with very helpful and friendly staff they couldn't do enough for you! Fresh coffee and coissonts in the morning! 2 mins away from travel options! Perfect stay will definitely staff there again!

The beauty of this hotel was unmatched- Quaint, charming, friendly and made the whole trip extra special. Quiet and delightful! Thank you for making my first trip to Paris so memorable. Will be back to stay here again always.

Absolutely helpful, pleasant staff. Very welcoming & sweet. Nice location, we enjoyed the local outdoor market & shops.
It was perfect for us. We would for sure come back to this place again. Thank you hotel Gaston’s staff 💗

Very nice and well decorated hotel. A perfect place when visit Paris. It’s quiet and well located (far enough from the crowd and close enough to walk around and enjoy the city). If you take a scooter, the Arc de Triomphe is five minutes away!

The Hotel Gaston is a wonderful Parisian hotel, the rooms are small (as typical for France), but the Gaston is fun and funky and the rooms are so very clean.

The staff at reception are so helpful and friendly. We enjoyed our week long stay very much. The breakfasts were awesome!! I enjoyed cheese, ham, yogurt and croissants every morning, and I certainly do miss them now that I'm home.

Coffee/espresso is offered 24/7.

Don't bring too much luggage, the elevator is very French and it is TINY! :-)

I'd enjoy another visit to Paris, and I'll likely stay at the Hotel Gaston even though it is not in the center of Paris. It's a quiet lovely neighborhood and there are some great places to eat.

My wife and I went with friends over to Paris for a weekend, staying the Friday and Saturday nights at the Gaston.

The receptionist was fast, efficient and friendly on arrival.

Room 606 was on the 6th floor - the lift could just comfortably fit 2 people and suitcases. We never had to wait more than 30’seconds for the lift.

606 is quite small with rudimentary storage and a pleasant enough view through the very tops of the plane trees. The bathroom was equally compact but well equipped. I’d advise caution when getting in the bath to shower, as it’s a little awkward climbing in. The bed was comfy enough but not massive!

There is simple breakfast in the hotel and free coffee all day.

There is a lounge downstairs from the reception that we only found out about just before we left.

The Rouergue bistro round the corner is highly recommended.

To Gard du Nord.

Hotel Gaston is located about a 5 minutes stroll from Pont Cardinet Station. It’s 1 stop on blue line L to Gare Sainte Lazare. It’s 3 levels down to Gare Haussmann Sainte-Lazare (through a shopping arcade with no signage to help!!) and 1 stop on the magenta line to Gare Magenta at Gare du Nord. This is not a great trip if you have kids and heavy suitcases in tow.

Another tip - get the app called Taxis Connect, as it is a fantastic way of ordering taxis in Paris.

Close to everything and staff is very nice, tiny elevator but that’s Europe. Lovely clean room. View from the terrace with opening doors is a nice perk. Says sound proof but sometimes the street can be quite loud.

Comfortable clean and quiet room. Friendly and efficient service and advice. Cheap and efficient transfer to CDG airport. 10 minutes walk from Metro and well stocked supermarket. Nice breakfast
with fresh fruit in the morning. Cappuccino available all day. A nice home from home!

A lovely warm welcome from all of the staff, who gave great advise on where to eat and using the Metro around Paris. The room was spotlessly clean, with a wonderfully comfy bed. The room was compact which you expect in Paris but the shower was actually in the room, which personally I didn't like (and never seen before!) hence only a 3 rating.

Made a last minute booking, all just worked out fine. Warm welcome by night staff, really apreaciated after a long day of travelling. Nice little hotel. Small breakfast restaurant, but it worked out fine.

Staff is amazing! Really took care of stuff and made us welcome. I will have no problem choosing this place again if I be in Paris. Also location is very convenient to a lots of tourist places. Morning breakfast in a great addition to overall stay!

I adore this hotel. Cute touches, kind, helpful staff and powerful air conditioning. Rooms were very clean and hotel was walkable to multiple metro stops! Included breakfast was also great! Thank you!!!

The hotel is very nice. The rooms are modern and clean. The staff is very helpfull is kind. The loctaion is near Montmartre (30 min walking and 15 min Uber). The breakfast is good but not extensive. Restaurant tip: Augustin.

Calling this a boutique hotel is probably a bit far fetched, but it is a small, nice hotel located in the 17th arrondissement of Paris. Service is perfect, really friendly and always helpful - bravo. Rooms are quite small and cramped, but that is perfectly normal in Paris ok. Hotel was very clean. Breakfast was a bit boring and nothing special - obviously a small number of guests does not justify a real buffet but it would be nice if they moved everything out of the wall corner and added fresh fruits f.ex. All in all a pleasant & recommendable place to stay in Paris.

Lovely three start hotel near Batignolles square, MLK park and park Monceau. Welcoming and well kept. Guitars in the basement lounge provided great entetertainment. Comfortable room for three that felt bigger than usual for Paris standards. AC worked great. Will come back!

We got a very good impression of the hotel Gaston.
Hotel is located very central and almost all sights can be reached on foot or by subway.
Staff is very friendly and helpful.
Room is small but nice and very clean.
Breakfast is sufficient.
At the next Paris Visit we will choose our hotel Gaston again.

Room is small but recently refurbished and clean. Comfy bed and a good shower. All staff were very friendly and helpful. Free coffee or tea in reception is a nice touch with paper cups to allow these to be taken to your room. Continental breakfast was absolutely fine. We had a rear facing room which was v quiet. location is 5 mins walk to railway station, 2 mins to bus stop, 10mins walk thru the village to metro. A wee bit out the way but priced accordingly. The small cafe on the corner sells metro/bus tickets, a pack of ten is 15euro. The village has a nice vibe on a Sunday morning which leads down to a flea market. Up at the railway station there is a newly developed area where there are modern bistros and cafes. This is Paris and for the money this is excellent

Very good breakfast, very friendly and helpful staff. Great thing there is an elevator. Is in an amazing district with a number of delicious patisseries, boucheries, cheese shops, bread shops and other gastronomic delights down the street. Is an affluent quieter area.
The small bathroom and close quarters make things a bit difficult. Only a half screen on the shower with no way to prevent flooding the floor. The drain is right where you would put your feet but if you step on the drain it plugs and floods the floor even worse. No refrigerator in the room (no room). But there is an awesome opening window (trade off).

Nice rooms, clean and very helpful staff åt the desk !
Breakfest absolutely ok. Good Price for a Nice hotel in Paris! Will recomend it for my friends!
A little far from the centre of paris but if youre off to walking you han reach arc the triumph in 25-30 min.

Staff superb, efficient and really friendly. Room just as needed, modern, clean and serviced each day.
Location very convenient & close to metro lines 2 & 3. I look forward to seeing you again soon. Thank you!

Small boutique hotel. Not central location but relatively quiet and 8 minutes walk from two Metro stations and an RER line C station so easy enough to get around. Internally the hotel is clean and tidy, and a little bit funky with their artwork. Rooms are small, typical of Paris, but refurbished to a good standard with very comfortable twin beds (not too firm and not too soft, felt a little like memory foam). Continental breakfast was basic but nice enough and not too expensive. Reception manned by two guys who were both very friendly, spoke perfect English and were very helpful. Overall recommend for a short break, if you are prepared to do a little walking

It was nice hotel, very helpful at the desk, clean, very convenient close to touristic places and good breakfast. Room clean and comfortable. It is close to metro station and 40 minutes far from the CDG airport.

worked great for a week in Paris. Front desk staff excellent. B-Fast okay, service there was great. I will be back. Location is nice. Rooms are basic but most everything you need. No Frig but I guess that is an american thing.JC

Hotel is Located in an ideal location for ease of access to the Metro for sightseeing.
The staff in the hotel are extremely helpful and cant do enough for you. Rooms are serviced every day and the beds are very comfortable. Continental breakfast is excellent. Special mention for Lui'e in reception for looking after us, first class service.

Booked stay at this hotel via Fleetway Travel. Arrived on Thursday 3/14, checked in at 2pm. Checked out Sunday 12pm, they kept our bags after checkout and we where able to return later that day to pick up our luggage for no extra cost. Breakfast was included, cute breakfast area. The staff is very friendly and helpful. Front desk helped us get taxis and help us with maps and directions till we got the hang of getting around the city. The front desk helped out in every way possible making our stay easier. The rooms were comfortable and always well serviced. Close to every attraction, just a Metro away. Great experience, great staff, recommended!

A nice cozy boutique hotel.Excellent staff at front desk.The bus takes you to the city centre from the door step luterally.I prefetred it to the metro as you get to see the city.The breakfast was good and we could eat around as the location of the hotel was very ideal.Get the rooms that open on the pierre avenue as the back side doesnt offer a good view.They arrNged an airlort shuttle on the way back.The stFf gave me numbers for ordering take away meals.The room was comfortable and good size.

My daughter and I returned to Hotel Gaston for a second visit in the early Spring after our previous November trip. She and I had decided to see Paris in both seasons and take our time with the sites we wanted to see. We love the neighborhood feel of the Gaston and everyone who works there is pleasant, accommodating and good resources for which direction to head as we go out the door: Merci beaucoup!

A few days before Valentine’s Day my wife found a travel offer to Paris. We had previously discussed going as I knew it was on her bucket list and I took a few semester of French in college and always wanted to visit. So we booked this deal which was round trip air with a hotel including breakfast. Lucky for us we were booked into Hotel Gaston, a little boutique hotel in a neighborhood setting a short walking distance to the Arc de Triomphe. We would also utilize taxis to further destinations on our excursions.
Upon arrival we were greeted by Luic. Since my French was not that good it was a relief that he spoke English.
The room was quite chic and comfortable, a bit small by excessive American standards, but perfect for our stay. The only thing that did not work for us was the USB port to charge our phones but we had a electrical adapter so it wasn’t an issuer for us and They said they would be repairing it right after we checked out.
The complimentary breakfast was good with a nice selection. A selection of different croissants and breads, salami, ham and cheeses, fresh fruit, cereals, yogurts, milk, fresh squeezed juices, and a coffe/espresso machine that was available 24 hours.
The home feel and hospitality of Jennifer & Luic, Who both spoke english, was outstanding!! I feel as if I now have two very good friends in Paris.
Since the weather was not completely cooperating with us during our stay we were not able to do everything we had wanted to do. The good part about that is now we will have to return to Paris and we will definitely stay with our friends at Hotel Gaston.

Hotel Gaston is awesome, super clean, amazing breakfast, comfy bed and best of all is the staff. The front desk, housekeeping, the breakfast attendants were all so helpful and made the trip perfect. The front desk arranged all of our transportation as well as giving us the best ideas of where to eat locally.

Cute little hotel in a residential neighborhood. The rooms are modern and clean, but EXTREMELY SMALL. The walls are very thin, which led to me hearing the elevator all night and my noisy neighbors. The staff was very friendly, but there is no full time housekeeping or room service. Overall, pretty good for the price but needs some work.

Great hotel in a fantastic location for people who never been to Paris. Price is reasonable and hotel is very clean. Will stay there again on another trip to Paris. People in Paris are very polite and the food is excellent.

Stayed here three nights visiting family in Paris. Booked package through Easyjet which was great value. Nice quirky hotel with excellent staff. Nice compact rooms with all amenities. Typically french continental breakfast,great quality with plenty of choice. Ideal hotel for a long weekend.

What a perfect and unique hotel in such a great and convenient location. Great staff and such a lovely place to stay... Highly recommend this place whether your stay is business or pleasure. I have been here twice now and wouldn't stay anywhere else now.

Very charming hotel in a quiet area about 20 minute walk from the Champs Elysee. The front desk staff was very friendly and helpful in checking us in when we arrived late in the night and in guiding us with things to see and do in the area. There are 2 bus stops close to the hotel, one that takes you to Champs Elysees and another that goes to the Opera House. Since we went in December, Paris was quite cold and we walked a couple of times but ended up taking the bus on the really cold days. The Metro is also close by but we did not really use it much. In better weather, I think it should be a lovely walk to the main attractions. The room was clean and breakfast was pretty decent. There is a cozy room to hangout with books to read. Also, there is a very nice Italian restaurant right across the street and a few other restaurants a couple of blocks away.
We very much enjoyed our stay here and would definitely come back.

Stayed here with my daughter. Hotel is quirky and I wanted to like it. Good location, short walk from metro and arc. But the service warrants a lower rating. My son was planning on coming in for one night and had a separate room booked through a travel agent. He had flight issues, so I asked if his room could be cancelled.. The women at the front desk said that since the reservation was made through a travel agency, we would have to work through them. We called the travel agency and were told that since there had been flight issues, they did not think it would be a problem, but they would have to check with the hotel. The travel agency called back and said they spoke with the hotel (and gave me the name of the same woman at the front desk I had spoken with initially) and that the hotel would not allow for a cancellation - we would have to pay for his room. It was after the time for cancellation, so I don't object to the hotel denying a cancellation, even for flight issues. But why didn't they tell me that when I asked in person - I wasted an hour of my time and made two international calls that could have been avoided. The young woman who worked at the breakfast buffet was also lacking in friendliness and effectively hurls items onto the buffet.

Delightful little Hotel, in a very quiet neighbourhood. Amazing staff, so friendly, nice clean room, excellent breakfast. Not too far from the Metro,, and a VERY good selection of Restaurants near by. Would definitely recommend this Hotel, I certainly hope to return

It was amazing! Paris is one of the most beautiful Citys in the World.Specially began our lovely trip to Paris when we checked in the Hotel. Hotel Gaston is placed central but quite by the traffic sounds. The Staff were always very friendly and made a great job. Our Room had a spectacular Design and the whole building was stocked a modern/cool arts. From the hotel, we could take the Metro or Bus to come very easy to the hotspots of Paris. Therefore we were able to enjoy our vacation in every part. Thank you very much, Hotel Gaston Staff!

Hi we have just returned from a three day mini break from Paris, we stayed in The hotel Gaston, which is situated to the North of Arc de Triomphe, about a twenty minute walk, the hotel is modern with a new feel to it, however the rooms are quite small, probably the smallest room i have ever stayed in, we had room 505 on the 5th floor, there were no tea and coffee making facilities in the room, however there was a machine in reception which was free to use, there is a small lift, capable of taking two people, which is not ideal when the maids are moving their linen, the room has a big window which lets in enough light, a clothes hanger instead of a wardrobe, a tv and a bathroom off the bedroom, which is even smaller, how they got a toilet shower and toilet in there is a miracle. the room was clean but not cleaned again while we were there, we had to ask for toilet roll and towels Reception was a desk with an attendant 24 hours a day, with a few tables to sit about 30 for breakfast, breakfast was as basic as you can get, continental breakfast was cold hard packet croissants with jams and a bread, three choices of cereal, two cooked meats and cheese, not great but we survived, the staff however are the reason we enjoyed our stay, they are helpful and pleasant with the exception of the girl who served breakfast, everyone else bent over backwards and helped book trips and hop on hop buses, the location is 18 minutes walk from Moulin rouge, 44 minutes walk from Eiffel tower so the location is a little too far out for my liking, it was a nice hotel but probably would not return

We were 4 days in Paris. The Hotel Gaston was perfect for this trip. It is a little and lovely hotel.The Gaston team is very friendly and helped for Taxi to airport and for other information.in 50 m of the hotel you have a China restaurant, Italiano restaurant and Brasserie + Cafe.

Quaint little hotel, walking distfrom the Arc de Triomphe. Great little bistros all around. Rooms are small, but fine for sleeping. Nice breakfast, very friendly and helpful staff. Would recommend . Great for the value

Lovely little hotel on the outskirts of Paris. Close to trains buses and metro. Good size room plus bathroom well decorated in and out. Continental breakfast was very good. Need was maid every day plus cleaned.

Nice little hotel nestled in the beautiful 17th Arrondissement very conveniently located in the city. Very nice and knowledgeable front desk staff. Very clean rooms and facilities. The bus stop is almost in front of the hotel and you can be either at the Opera or the main train station in less than 20 minutes. Will definitely come back to this hotel!!!

The hotel is a 3* plus plus plus, really superior Staff is excellent, professional, very kind and always available. The breakfast is really genuine and with high quality products. Rooms are nice and wery well designed

Extremely helpful and friendly staff. Loved the decor and lighting. Lovely area of Paris with some fabulous bars and restaurants nearby. Airport shuttle service was brilliant too as it made getting back to the airport quick and easy.

My large family stayed here for over a week on vacation. The staff was incredible! Always super friendly and helpful. The rooms were small but clean and the morning breakfast was excellent. We had a great time! Will definitely stay again!

Small Room without a wardrobe, very tiny bathroom. Fantastic comfortable kingsize bed. You can have breakfast in the hotel. Friendly and helpfull staff, 24h hour reception. The best croissant bakery in Paris around the corner: Maison Julien Les Saveurs de Wagram, 169 Avenue de Wagram

The hotel is located close to city centre, since my meetings were in the area, it was great location for me. Rooms are pretty small, but have comfy bed and all you need for short stay - fast Wifi, good bathroom amenities and air-condition for hot summer. Excellent staff at reception, always helpful to assist with restaurant and taxi bookings. Nice continental breakfast with fresh products. Happy to be back once in Paris again.

My wife and I stayed at this boutique hotel in the last weekend of September. The hotel is located in a quiet and cozy neighborhood in the 17th arrondissement. Easy arrival via taxi from the airport (50 euros), about 30 minutes drive, well worth it! We were met by a very cheerful service minded receptionist who gave us useful tips on were to eat lunch nearby. The rooms are small but practical with good standard and comfortable bed. We asked for a room on the upper floors (5th floor), number 506, that was very nice. The breakfast is simple but extremely good! Fresh orange juice, croissants, baguette, cheese and meat condiments. And a coffee machine. You get everything you need for a good start to your day. We stayed two nights (Friday to Sunday) and booked via their own webpage so we got a discount and wine and macrons in the room of arrival. Very nice touch! We’ll definitely stay here the next time we visit Paris!

I thought the area was great, clean hotel. Rooms very small but clean and affordable. I would recommend this hotel and would go return. Restaurants across the street both ways were delicious and had great food and service.

I visited the hotel on a business trip. Due to its location, the simple but comfortable rooms and the nice breakfast I would recommend this hotel to every business travel who wants to stay in Paris city center at an affordable rate

The Gaston is a wonderful place to stay in the 17th arrondisement. It is a beautiful area and extremely quiet with excellent bistros and boulangeries. The rooms at the Gaston, while small, are spotless and comfortable. The bed was excellent and the use of space was extremely well thought out. There is also an excellent breakfast which started at 7 am which made it very welcome for early morning travelers. The staff could not have been more helpful. We would definitely stay at the Gaston again. We loved it.

We stayed here for 4 nights for a city break to see all the Paris sights. Ideal location near metro station and 20 minute walk from Arc de Triomphe. Rooms are small but this seems to be the standard in Paris. Reception all very friendly and helpful. Breakfast pleasant continental affair. Would recommend 👍

I cannot say enough good things about the accommodations, staff, location and overall experience at this hotel. It is modern, clean, quiet and situated in a lovely neighborhood setting. The metro is a breeze to get to and there are lots of local shops, restaurants and markets close by. The wonderful women staff of the hotel (Jennifer, Leticia and E) are truly the very best at their jobs and were helpful in making some of the best suggestions for my trip. I will certainly be returning to Paris and the hotel Gaston again.

all services all the staff, specially Jennifer Touitou who give us very good information and trips recommendation Always with a beautiful smile.the space on room very clean and area is close to tourist sites.

We stayed here for our honeymoon and though it is a bit outside the main attractions of Paris, we could walk - about a 20-30 min. walk to the very centre of the city. It was nice and quiet and the breakfast was simple but lovely. The rooms were very small but it is a boutique hotel, so we really didn't expect anything else - just enough room for two people.

We just came back from 8 nights at Hotel Gaston. The staff were so friendly & accommodating. The hotel is so cute. The only issue we had was with the plumbing and the shower in particular. The drain kept clogging up very quickly so taking a shower longer than 5 mins was not an option.
The hotel is located in a quieter residential area which is quite sweet, but can a little challenging when you're tired from walking all day. We had to take the Metro back several times. Overall, great stay!!

Visited with my two children and 72 year old mother for 3 night break. The staff were amazing and couldn't do enough for us. Very clean throughout. Lovely continental breakfast and good selection of hot drinks. Very close to metro and safe area for walking around. We all really enjoyed our stay and would go back there.

The location is superb and the hotel is great! Clean rooms, good breakfast and and a helpful staff. The reception is open 24 hours which makes late check-in possible. We are so happy with our stay here.

Staff were so friendly and very helpful, breakfast tasted great, room was clean, nice and perfect size for the two of us. Location was fab, we were a 20 minute walk from the Arc de Triumph and an hour walk from the Eiffel Tower, it was a €13 Uber ride to the Louvre. Honestly can’t recommend this hotel enough, we are definitely coming back, they couldn’t have made us feel more welcome!

We stayed over a weekend at the Hotel Gaston for the first time.
We were surprised about the great service during check in as well as check out; very friendly and helpful!
We received a lot of insights, tips and information about the public transportation.
The room was clean and looked quite new. As always in Paris, the room could have been bigger.
Breakfast was great, with good (!) coffee, croissants, bread, ... and fresh orange juice.
All in all, great hotel for a reasonable price!

This is the third time that I have stayed at this property. Booking and check in went fine and hotel pricing was fair. This hotel is in a residential area of the 17th and it is generally quiet. There is Metro access is not too far and shops within the area. The room was Paris small and clean although the overall room feel was a bit dated (rustic Ikea). Opportunities are: acknowledge repeat guests (we have a choice where we stay ), and PLEASE have more variety in the breakfast (there was no change to the menu for our entire 4 day stay). All of the interactions with the staff were nice and professional. Based on my overall experience I would probably stay elsewhere on my next Paris visit.

I chose this hotel based on room size, number/ size of beds, (queen and a twin) and location. What I was given was a room half the size I reserved and a broken cot for my son to sleep on. I complained and after showing what I booked and much debate. In the end they made it good with two rooms. Which the one room had a broken shower head.
The staff was very polite and I believe this was all issue with booking.com
The location was very pleasant. It was a simple light breakfast.

The room was barely large enough for two people to walk around the bed to get to the bathroom—-a couple hooks for hanging up clothes—- good for staying a night or two; a little out of the way for seeing the sights— around 20 euro taxi ride to Eiffel Tower, le louvre area— the staff was really nice 👍

I was taking my grandson on his first trip to Paris. Room small but very clean and pleasant. Got twin beds as requested and room ready early when we arrived. Thankful for air conditioning which worked very well and had individual room controls. Lovely view to trees. Staff very cheerful, kind and helpful (finding restaurants, getting us ice, calling taxi, giving advice on how to best get places).

We were only in Paris for one day/night for a layover so I found this hotel ahead of time & booked online. It was hard to find the "right" hotel for just a night but I wanted something that said Paris. Hotel Gaston did not disappoint us! This was not a huge hotel but the pictures of the rooms & hallways got my attention. We felt safe walking in the neighborhood that night. Walking distance to the Arc de Triomphe & plenty of restaurants. The room was a little small as to be expected in Europe but still was plenty enough for the two of us & our luggage, very cozy. The view from our room #402 was wonderful to see the beautiful buildings across the street. We found the hotel, room, bed, bathroom & breakfast area all to be very comfortable. The staff were very friendly explaining the metro location & getting us a cab the next morning. This was a great choice for us & a wonderful way to end our trip.

Nice hotel, good breakfast for 3***. Good area in Paris for biz trips. Not many tourists. But in the bathroom it was film tape on the shower tap...and also on the socket. Hope they renovate the rooms.

Our room was a little small. There was not enough room between the bed and wall for a suitcase or for a person to walk.
But our room was nice and tidy each day. Breakfast was good and the staff was very kind and helpful. Definitely suggest this hotel.

First time at Hotel Gaston, Excellent...very nice staffs, comfortable and very good breakfast....luvvvvvved the location as it was quiet but well situated to walk everywhere ...we were very happy and will be back

LOCATION: safe and good neighborhood. Very good boulangery, fromagery, cafe etc... nearby. Bus 31 10 min to ARC DE TRIUMPH
But the most important very freandly highly professional service. Starting from the booking, breakfast, rooms ...
So thank you very much HOTEL GASTON. Hope to be your guest again.

It is a small boutique hotel but very comfortable and clean. Good mattress and pillows and A/C which is what you need after long days of sightseeing. Staff very courteous and friendly. Would definitely recommend.

The hotel is very small - small lobby, 2-person elevator, small breakfast area. They have a basement sitting area and some bathrooms but it was very dingy. Our room was super tiny - we had 2 large suitcases and 1 carry-on and it was always a challenge to access our clothes. The bathroom was nice and modern. A/C was nice. Breakfast was not worth $12.50 per person. The croissants were stale, the options very limited. They ran out of sliced cheese one day and put processed cheese instead. The day we were leaving we left 1 hour before breakfast was served. I asked if we could just help ourselves as mostly everything was setup - but front desk person said no - we paid for the breakfast and could not eat.

The hotel is nice, in a good "arrondissement" (17eme) , quiet and safe. The hotel is small , modern and clean . The room is enough with a clean and modern bathroom.
People were very nice. Breakfast is good as a buffet one with everythinh is need to have a good breakfast.

This hotel is in a very family friendly area (there must be a school or nursery near by) as there are many families or parents with young ones walking around the area. It feels very safe and relaxing. The hotel is near lots of restaurants, as well as the required bakeries for early morning breakfast. The only minor issue was lack of near by grocery stores like a monoprix, but since we were there only a couple of nights, it wasn't a deal breaker.

The hotel itself was clearly renovated and runs a tad smaller than average, but still good. Defintely not NYC or Tokyo small, but getting close. I especially like the effort to make it more a Joie de Vivre style decor with different styles on each floor. They offered breakfast, but we didn't partake in it. The beds and the room itself was all good. I loved the two bottles of mineral water and the personalized touches with the card and the cookies. Service was excellent and the staff awesome.

Some possible things for the hotel to think about
1) It didn't appear to have a bar in the main lobby, could be due to size or some regulations, but it would have made for a nice relaxing pre dinner hang out with some beer or wine.
2) I love the fact that there was a nespresso machine there, but it often ran out of water or the coffee capsules. There wasn't a clear way to get access to water either, tap water is great in Paris.
3) A couple of the room's safe didn't work, we didn't raise this as we used one of the other room's safe to store the passports. But it would be good for them to spot check the safes
4) The basement lounge area is too dark and could use a bit more décor. Need access to water and glasses to make it a place for people to relax and drink some wine/beer/water

For other travellers
1) We were used to getting everywhere by metro and so when we first arrived via Wagram, it was a longer walk than previous other hotels in Paris. In hindsight, we should have taken the bus as there are two nearby stops (53 and 31) that would have brought us closer to the hotel. This is by far the easiest choice as there are usually far fewer steps to walk up and down to the metro. You will want to take advantage of the bus/metro combo to get to Gard du Nord on your way to CDG(via RER B)
2) Amazing indian food near by (Royal Indien), decent Korean across the street.
3) Arc de Triomphe is technically walkable (25min), so pretty good location

Great boutique hotel in a lovely area, bus stop just 1/2 block away and with access to train and metro/subway within 10 min walk.
kudos to their front desk and breakfast staff, they made our stay lovely.
as expected room is small but has what you need.
thanks again and will come back
LO:) & GM

Great hotel in quite corner of the city, away from crowds and just walking distance to Arc de Triomphe, Champs-Élysées. Rooms are small - just like everything in " the old continent", but very clean and well maintained. Good breakfast served daily from 7am - 10am. Exceptional staff , always ready to help with any concerns. Highly recommended, will stay again.

Very tight unconfortable room, no furniture! Only 1 person taking care of breakfast (unclean tables). Poor variety of meal. Recommendation from staff unreliable (2 nearby restaurants recommended for dinner on Sunday - both have closing day on Sundays). We were a little bit disappointed... :-(

We had multiple family members staying at Hotel Gaston. One set of family had a travel snafu and with Jennifer's help it was seamless. What a relief!!
This is a clean, secure and quaint hotel. The staff are extremely helpful with information and setting up tours and taxis. I love that it's close to everything but far enough to have that village or neighborhood feel.
I will stay here again I'm sure!

Visited with the family in March 2018. The hotel was boutique-like with a great staff, clean rooms, and nicely upgraded bathrooms. The weather was rainy and the hotel provided umbrellas along with help with directions, tips, etc.

The hotel is a bit far from the major tourist attractions. Not bad for those who want to walk.

Arrived last Sunday have stayed here before, ideally situated in the really good part of the city it’s very close for buses and Metro which is a must if you are here either for business or leisure. The hotel itself is wonderful, beautiful rooms, nice comfy beds. They offer continental breakfast which is fine with fresh fruit yoghurts etc and they cater for vegetarians or other dietary requirements. If you don’t want to go out and eat at the many good local restaurants they do offer light snacks ie soups or you can bring in your own takeaway and eat it. Wine as well as soft drinks are available which is handy! All in all I can’t speak highly enough of the place staff and Management are exceptional all are very professional and they speak several languages. Shall continue to come here everything you need at really good hotel rates.

Staff were lovely at check in and even helped us to arrange a tour of the eiffle tower, explain how to get to the running expo to collect my number and how to get to the start in the morning. Room was clean and tidy. Only downside was we could hear the lift going up and down. FAB location and would recommend!

Stayed here from 7th-9th April to partake in the Paris marathon. The hotel is very basic and extremely small. I was sharing with a friend and so we decided to pull the two single beds apart. They are actually smaller than single beds and so if you roll over you will virtually fall out of the bed. The pillows however are really fluffy and comfy. There is a desk one side and a small area to hang a few items of clothing with three shelves underneath. The bathroom is also small with an open shower. The large shower head would not remain upright on the wall bracket due to it being so large. So I had to hold this whenever I showered. The water would also would be so powerful that the whole bathroom would be soaked.
There was a safe and a small Juliette balcony.
The Croisants at breakfast were amazing but I do not thing that the breakfast was worth €12. The dining area is set back a little way from the reception and entrance.
When you leave the hotel you are to leave your room key at reception. This is not safe in my opinion as my friend arrived back one afternoon before me and was told that I was already up in the room (I wasn't). Another evening there was a note to say that they were away for 5 minutes. We got fed up of waiting and so helped ourselves to our keys.
All in all this hotel suited my needs for the marathon as it was clean and relatively comfortable. However I would not choose to book here again for the cost.

Good bed ! Correct check-in with a warm welcome, very kind people, clean room. cleaning every day of our stay. Good service (umbrella's available), maps, and good information concerning metro, bus, train etc.

The rooms in this hotel are unbelievably small. While the staff was polite and friendly this place is pretty far from all the tourist attractions. The area around the hotel was also a bit scary to walk at night. The breakfast was the worst we had in all the places we have been. THEY DON'T HAVE A KITCHEN!! all they offered was stale bread and 5 fruits for the entire hotel on first come first serve. We did not even realize there were fruits until the last day because they never refill!
